•  Core Philosophy: Simplicity above all. Never over-engineer.
•  Always prefer small, focused functions over large complex ones.
•  Never create new classes, services, or abstractions unless absolutely necessary.
•  Use clear, descriptive names. No cryptic abbreviations.
•  Strictly follow the existing folder structure: core/, features/chat/, features/memory/.
•  UI code should remain clean and minimal.
•  When the user says “keep it simple”, take it very literally.
•  Do not put any business logic inside widgets.
•  Do not add new packages without explicit permission.
•  When building new features, start with the simplest possible implementation.
